@1807   = ~Saving the Forest of Tethir

You have defeated the ancient dragon, Thundercracker saved the lives of both the elves and werewolves of the Forest of Tethir.~

@1808 = ~Garrick is missing!

The bard Garrick suddenly disappeared somewhere. Among his belongings was a letter from a certain Thomas Ritch, who threatened him and made an appointment at the Copper Coronet.~

@1809 = ~Garrick is missing!

In the back rooms of the Copper Coronet, we saw signs of a struggle. Obviously something happened there. We need to find the one who called Garrick to a meeting. It sounds like it was another bard, that apparently, is in the area of the Five Flagons tavern.~

@1810 = ~Garrick is missing!

In the Five Flagons tavern we found Thomas Ritch, the bard who was blackmailing Garrick. It turned out that he sold him into slavery to a Calimshan merchant named Garib. We need to find Garib at the City Gates before he leaves town. ~

@1811 = ~Garrick is missing!

We found and freed Garrick. This epic story has come to an end.~

@1812 = ~Monkey Trouble

Borivyk, an animal dealer from the Water Gardens, asked us to get medicine for his monkey named Pepper. The medicine can be prepared by the priestess of the Water Garden Temple, her name is D'nala Shalandalan.~

@1813 = ~Monkey Trouble

We spoke to the priestess D'nala Shalandalan and she gave us the cure. It should be taken to Borivyk, the animal dealer in the Water Gardens, to heal his monkey.~

@1814 = ~Monkey Trouble

It was a rather strange task, but as a result, we still managed to cure Pepper, the monkey from the Water Gardens! This deed will not be sung by bards in taverns, but the soul is calmer now.~

@1815 = ~Bear Trouble

Borivyk, an animal dealer from the Water Gardens, asked us to find someone to look after the pet she-bear. Perhaps one of the rangers or druids would fit the role. But you should definitely not look in Athkatla.~

@1816 = ~Bear Trouble

We found a ranger who agreed to look after the she-bear. I hope they get along and my task is done.~

@1817  = ~Bear Trouble

We found a ranger who agreed to look after the she-bear. Now I can return to Borivyk.~

@1818 = ~Meeting Silke

We met an old acquaintance of Silke Rosena at the "Five Flagons". By some miracle, she had survived that confrontation in Beregost, and she had arranged another surprise for Garrick - a very unpleasant one. Perhaps we will meet again.~

